ðŸ”¹ Part 1: Strings
Notes:

Strings are immutable (you cannot change them in place).

Common operations: slicing, searching, replacing, formatting.

Useful methods: .lower(), .upper(), .strip(), .split(), .join(), .replace().


Part 2: Dictionaries
Notes:

Dictionary = key-value pairs.

Keys must be immutable (string, int, tuple).

Values can be anything (list, dict, object).



âœ… Step 1: Hints (Think Before Seeing Solutions)
Easy

